= git reset =
[[git-restore]], [[git-switch]], [[git-show]]

== COMMAND FORM ==
    git reset <COMMIT>[:<TREE>] [--] <PATHSPEC>
    git reset [--soft | --hard] <COMMIT>

Annoyingly first form ONLY resets STAGING AREA

== EXAMPLES ==
    git reset --hard HEAD
    git reset 0f463b:dir1/dir2 -- *.card

== OPTIONS ==
	--soft    # ONLY moves HEAD
                similar to [[git-switch]] but does not update/change any files
	--hard    # resets both STAGING AREA and WORKING TREE
